---

<Base title={title} description={description} schema={schema}>
  <section class="px-4 py-12">
    <div class="prose">
      <h1>About SEO Leeds — Our Approach to Search Marketing</h1>

      <div class="quick-answer">
        <p>SEO Leeds is a data-led search marketing agency. We operate across Leeds and West Yorkshire with a methodology built on technical depth, local market intelligence, and measurable commercial outcomes. Every engagement starts with data. Every deliverable ties to revenue.</p>
      </div>

      <p>SEO Leeds exists to solve a specific problem: the gap between what most agencies promise and what they actually deliver. The UK SEO market generates over £4 billion annually. A significant share of that spend produces reports full of vanity metrics — impressions, ranking fluctuations, traffic graphs — with no connection to revenue. We take a different approach. We measure organic search performance against commercial KPIs: enquiries generated, pipeline value created, and revenue closed.</p>

      <p>We work with businesses across every sector represented in the Leeds economy. Professional services firms around Wellington Place. Technology companies at Leeds Dock. Retailers operating from Trinity Leeds and the Victoria Quarter. Healthcare practices in the suburbs. Hospitality venues across the city centre. Each sector carries distinct search dynamics, competitive pressures, and compliance requirements. Our methodology adapts to all of them because it starts from data, not assumptions.</p>

      <h2>Our Methodology</h2>

      <p>Our process follows four phases. Each phase produces documented deliverables with defined KPIs.</p>

      <h3>Phase 1: Technical Foundation</h3>

      <p>Every engagement opens with a technical audit. We assess site architecture, crawl efficiency, render behaviour, Core Web Vitals, structured data coverage, internal link topology, and indexation status. Technical deficiencies are the single largest source of invisible ranking loss. A site with 40% crawl waste cannot outperform a competitor running at 95% efficiency, regardless of content quality or link profile. We quantify the gap and close it first.</p>

      <p>Our audits cover 200+ technical checkpoints. We assess how search engines — and increasingly, large language models — parse, index, and surface content. Sites that fail to communicate structure through clean HTML, comprehensive schema markup, and logical information architecture lose visibility to competitors that do.</p>

      <h3>Phase 2: Market and Keyword Intelligence</h3>

      <p>We analyse search demand at the postcode level. Leeds LS1 through LS29 each carry distinct search patterns. A homeowner in Horsforth searches differently from a procurement manager at a Wellington Place firm. We map intent clusters, identify gaps in competitor coverage, and prioritise keywords by commercial value — not search volume alone. A 50-search-per-month term that converts at 8% outperforms a 2,000-search term that converts at 0.3%.</p>

      <p>This phase also covers competitor benchmarking. We reverse-engineer the top 10 results for every target keyword: content depth, link profile composition, domain authority trajectory, and structured data deployment. The output is a prioritised opportunity map with estimated traffic and revenue projections.</p>

      <h3>Phase 3: Content and Authority</h3>

      <p>Content strategy follows directly from the intelligence phase. Every page we create or optimise targets a specific intent cluster, carries the appropriate schema markup, and links into a defined topical hierarchy. We do not produce content in isolation. Each piece strengthens the site's topical authority across the full semantic territory.</p>

      <p>Link acquisition operates on the same principle. We pursue contextually relevant placements from domains with genuine authority in the target vertical. No PBNs. No link farms. No paid placements dressed up as editorial. The link profile we build survives algorithm updates because it reflects genuine authority signals.</p>

      <h3>Phase 4: Measurement and Iteration</h3>

      <p>We deploy server-side analytics, conversion tracking, and attribution modelling from day one. Every action maps to a measurable outcome. Monthly reporting covers keyword positions, organic traffic segmented by intent, local pack visibility, conversion events, and attributed revenue. Quarterly reviews assess strategy performance against projections and adjust priorities based on what the data shows — not what we expected it to show.</p>

      <h2>Technical Capabilities</h2>

      <p>Our technical practice covers the full stack of search infrastructure.</p>

      <p><strong>Crawl and indexation management.</strong> We configure crawl budgets, resolve duplicate content at scale, implement canonical strategies, manage JavaScript rendering requirements, and ensure search engines index exactly the pages that matter. For large sites — 10,000 pages and above — this discipline alone can unlock 30-50% more indexed pages within 90 days.</p>

      <p><strong>Structured data and schema.</strong> We implement JSON-LD markup across Organization, LocalBusiness, Service, FAQ, HowTo, Article, Product, and Review types. Correct schema increases rich result eligibility and provides AI search systems with the structured signals they need to cite your content.</p>

      <p><strong>Core Web Vitals and page experience.</strong> We optimise Largest Contentful Paint, Cumulative Layout Shift, and Interaction to Next Paint. Google's page experience signals are confirmed ranking factors. We treat them as engineering problems with measurable solutions, not vague aspirations.</p>

      <p><strong>AI search readiness.</strong> Google AI Overviews, ChatGPT search, Perplexity, and Copilot now source answers from the open web. Sites that structure content for extraction — clear entity definitions, factual claims with supporting data, well-marked FAQ sections — appear in these responses. Sites that do not get bypassed. We prepare for both paradigms simultaneously.</p>

      <h2>Leeds Market Expertise</h2>

      <p>Leeds is the largest economy in West Yorkshire and the second-largest financial centre in the UK outside London. The city contributes over £29 billion to regional GVA. Since Channel 4 relocated to South Bank, the digital and creative sector has grown at twice the national average. The legal sector employs over 30,000 professionals. The NHS and university complex anchors healthcare and education spending.</p>

      <p>That economic breadth creates a search landscape with unusual complexity. A family law firm in the city centre competes against 40+ practices for the same local pack positions. An independent retailer at the Corn Exchange faces national e-commerce brands in organic results. A SaaS company at Platform — the former Tetley brewery — targets global keywords from a Leeds base. Each scenario demands a distinct strategy built on local competitive intelligence, not generic playbooks.</p>

      <p>We track the Leeds search market continuously. We monitor competitor movements, local algorithm updates, Google Business Profile changes, and shifts in search behaviour across West Yorkshire postcodes. When a new development like the South Bank regeneration or the expansion of the Leeds Innovation District changes local search patterns, we adjust strategies before the competition notices.</p>

      <p>Our coverage extends across West Yorkshire: Bradford, Wakefield, Huddersfield, Halifax, and Harrogate. But Leeds is our primary market, and that depth of knowledge compounds over time. We have mapped the search dynamics for over 50 Leeds-specific industry verticals. That institutional knowledge accelerates every new engagement.</p>

      <h2>Our Process</h2>

      <p>Engagements follow a structured sequence designed to deliver measurable outcomes within the first 90 days.</p>

      <p><strong>Week 1-2:</strong> Technical audit, competitor analysis, and keyword intelligence. Deliverable: a prioritised action plan with projected impact estimates.</p>

      <p><strong>Week 3-4:</strong> Technical fixes deployed. Quick wins implemented. Content brief development begins. Analytics and tracking infrastructure verified or installed.</p>

      <p><strong>Month 2-3:</strong> Content production and deployment. Link acquisition initiated. Local SEO and Google Business Profile optimisation executed. First monthly report delivered with baseline benchmarks established.</p>

      <p><strong>Month 4+:</strong> Ongoing optimisation, reporting, and strategy refinement. Quarterly business reviews assess ROI against agreed targets and recalibrate priorities.</p>

      <h2>Reporting Approach</h2>

      <p>Reports exist to inform decisions, not to justify invoices. Every monthly report we deliver follows the same structure: what we did, what changed, what it means commercially, and what we plan to do next.</p>

      <p>We report on rankings segmented by intent category — navigational, informational, transactional, and local. Raw position data without intent context is meaningless. A position 3 ranking on a transactional keyword with 500 monthly searches and a 6% conversion rate is worth more than a position 1 ranking on an informational keyword with 5,000 searches and a 0.1% conversion rate. Our reports reflect that reality.</p>

      <p>All clients receive access to a live dashboard. Data refreshes daily. No waiting until the end of the month to see movement. If something requires attention between reports, we flag it proactively rather than waiting for the next scheduled review.</p>

      <h2>Engagement Models</h2>

      <p><strong>Ongoing retainer.</strong> Monthly SEO management with continuous optimisation, reporting, and strategic guidance. No lock-in contracts. Clients stay because the work delivers, not because of contractual obligation. That structure keeps us accountable every month.</p>

      <p><strong>Project-based.</strong> Defined scope, fixed timeline, agreed deliverables. Technical audits, site migrations, content programmes, or local SEO launches. Suited to businesses with specific objectives and internal teams that can execute recommendations.</p>

      <p><strong>One-off audit.</strong> Comprehensive assessment of technical health, content gaps, competitive position, and opportunity sizing. Delivered as an actionable document, not a generic checklist. Useful for businesses evaluating their current agency or considering SEO investment for the first time.</p>

      <p>Full service details on our <a href="/services/">services page</a>. Transparent pricing on our <a href="/seo-pricing-leeds/">SEO pricing page</a>.</p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is SEO Leeds?</h3>
        <p>SEO Leeds is a data-led search marketing agency serving businesses across Leeds and West Yorkshire. We specialise in technical SEO, local search optimisation, AI search readiness, and conversion-focused content strategy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What services does SEO Leeds provide?</h3>
        <p>Technical SEO audits, local SEO, Google Business Profile management, content strategy, AI search optimisation, structured data implementation, link acquisition, and ongoing management. Full details on our <a href="/services/">services page</a>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Does SEO Leeds only work with companies in Leeds?</h3>
        <p>Leeds and West Yorkshire are our primary market, but we work with businesses across the UK. Our deepest expertise covers Leeds, Bradford, Wakefield, Huddersfield, Harrogate, and the wider Yorkshire region.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How does SEO Leeds track and report results?</h3>
        <p>We track organic traffic, keyword positions, local pack visibility, conversion rates, and revenue attributed to organic search. Monthly reports benchmark all KPIs against agreed targets with full transparency on actions taken.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I review past campaign results?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Visit our <a href="/case-studies/">case studies page</a> for documented campaigns, the methodology applied, and the measurable outcomes achieved for Leeds businesses.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do I request a proposal from SEO Leeds?</h3>
        <p>Email hello@seo-leeds.uk or submit a request through our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>. We provide a complimentary site audit and consultation with no obligation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-box">
        <h2>Request a Proposal</h2>
        <p>We start every engagement with a complimentary audit and a data-backed assessment of your search opportunity. No obligation. No jargon. Just the numbers and a clear plan to act on them.</p>
        <p><a href="/contact/">Request a Proposal</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
